passing multiple args by position

changes made to a parameter value within a function does not affect the argument
    - know as pass by value
    - provide unidirection comms

Global variable: created outside of all functions , can be acced by any statemt in the program file
within a function

if to make a funciton global just do -> global variable_name

myValue = 10

def showValue():
    print(myValue)

def main():
    global myValue
    myValue= 9
    showValue()

main()